103. Create a very simple pageview counter by using ‘isset’ to check if the pageview variable has
already been created.
code:
<?php
// Start session to track pageviews
session_start();

// Check if pageview counter exists
if(isset($_SESSION['pageview'])) {
    // Increment counter
    $_SESSION['pageview']++;
} else {
    // Initialize counter for new session
    $_SESSION['pageview'] = 1;
}

// Display pageview count
echo "<h2>Pageview Counter</h2>";
echo "You have visited this page <b>" . $_SESSION['pageview'] . "</b> times in this session.";
?>
